reviewText: If you loved Aladdin, this is a must to add to your collection.

Item was in great condition.  I loved the Aladdin movies, and was pleased with this purchase.  It also came with the Disney Movie rewards points code, and the digital copy for your ultrviolet accounts, which is great.  Now I can own three copies of these movies, the Blu-ray, DVD, and the copy for the cloud.  These movies are classics, especially the first.  Rest in peace to Robin Williams. We all love you!  Without a doubt, I recommend!!!!
Love the sequels to Aladdin! Love all the animated Disney movies!

I know these movies were low-budget, straight-to-video productions, but it would've been nice to get better quality transfers on this Blu-Ray. It's definitely an upgrade from VHS, but the image quality still seems a bit blurry for Blu-Ray, like they just put the DVD versions on Blu-Ray. Also, maybe it's my imagination, but the movies look a little dim.
How Long Disney Aladdin The Return of Jafar / Aladdin and the King of Thieves 2-Movie Collection DVD & Blu Ray Returns
Great quality. Can't wait to see a goofy movie come out on blue ray
I was so thrilled to see both movies together on Blu Ray/DVD. I grew up watching these. They came fast and it's even more fun watching as an adult.

I am disappointed in these Blu-ray's they are not a great improvement over the DVD's that came with the set.  The only a little bit better.  The main problem with is 5.1 audio.  I tested this audio vs the DVD versions and the DVD 5.1 Dolby Digital is better than the Blu-rays DTS 5.1 track.  You lose more sounds in Blu-ray version.  I  will probably take the audio from the DVD's and create a bluray with DVD audio.

These are dvd movies on a bluray disc. I expected better quality, but no.
To keep or not to keep, I'll think about it. I'm just disappointed with this.
I just got this in the mail today. And because of this, I'm officially finished with my Aladdin Blu Ray collection. Tom And Jerry, The Lion King, Popeye,and Looney Tunes, you're all next!
Love how these have both a blu day and regular DVD versions of these movies. I also love how nothing really changes, it's the same as when I watched them as a child!
